<problem id="fs-idm142780240">
<para id="fs-idm30617472">What is an ecosystem service that performs the same function as a pesticide?</para>
<list id="fs-idp36748544" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha">
<item>pollination</item>
<item>secondary plant compounds</item>
<item>crop diversity</item>
<item>predators of pests</item>
</list>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm20843968"><label/>
<para id="fs-idp133405136">D</para></solution>
</exercise>
</section>
<section id="fs-idp94971120" class="critical-thinking">
<title>Critical Thinking Questions</title>
<exercise id="fs-idm31196944"><problem id="fs-idp51958976">
<para id="fs-idm56616048">Explain how biodiversity loss can impact crop diversity.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-idm169984000"><label/>
<para id="fs-idp39513328">Crop plants are derived from wild plants, and genes from wild relatives are frequently brought into crop varieties by plant breeders to add valued characteristics to the crops. If the wild species are lost, then this genetic variation would no longer be available.</para></solution></exercise>
<exercise id="fs-idp2467040"><problem id="fs-idm60897856">
<para id="fs-idp2474688">Describe two types of compounds from living things that are used as medications.</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-idm1942800"><label/>
<para id="fs-idm141365376">Secondary plant compounds are toxins produced by plants to kill predators trying to eat them; some of these compounds can be used as drugs. Animal toxins such as snake venom can also be used as drugs. (Alternate answer: antibiotics are compounds produced by bacteria and fungi which can be used to kill bacteria.)</para></solution></exercise>
</section>
